title: 1,119 people received digital nomad status in Kyrgyzstan since Sept 2022
body:
AKIPRESS.COM - Kyrgyzstan is implementing a pilot project Digital Nomad since September 2022 to attract highly qualified workers to the country and the development of high-tech sectors of the economy, reported the Ministry of Labor.

Citizens of six countries including Russia, Kazakhstan, Belarus, Azerbaijan, Armenia and Moldova working in software engineering, media, digital art, graphic and multimedia design, development of IT-products, artificial intelligence and robotics, programming computer and mobile games, and cybersport can get the status of the digital nomad.

Since the project start, 2,989 people applied for the status. 1,119 of them were given the status, the rest are waiting either for application processing or were rejected due to incomplete documents.
